<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="318" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1477,2008]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1477,1503]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lu, Y. - H." box="[280,404,1477,1504]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" pagination="1 - 453" refId="ref45640" refString="Lu, Y. - H. (1975) Ordovician trilobite faunas of central and southwestern China. Palaeontologia Sinica, New Series B, 11, 1 - 453." type="journal article" year="1975">Lu’s (1975</bibRefCitation>
, p. 318–9) diagnosis is still largely appropriate. It should be modified to include the inverted U shape of the wide hypostomal fork, and to emphasise that the pygidial ring furrows are transverse, rather than chevron–shaped. Despite the thin cuticle, the terrace ridges on the pygidial doublure are particularly strong. Only the best-preserved material shows a pointed junction of the facial sutures on the midline. In most flattened material the sutures appear to run nearly marginally over their anterior course.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="319" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1477,2008]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1437,150,897]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="319" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1657,1683]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reed" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[342,601,1657,1683]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="birmanicus">
<emphasis box="[342,601,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Birmanites birmanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally referred by 
<bibRefCitation author="Reed, F. R. C." box="[920,1062,1657,1684]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" pagination="1 - 98" refId="ref46807" refString="Reed, F. R. C. (1915) Supplementary Memoir on new Ordovician and Silurian fossils from the Northern Shan States. Palaeontologia Indica, New Series 6, 1 - 98." type="book chapter" year="1915">Reed (1915)</bibRefCitation>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte, 1876" authorityName="Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte" authorityYear="1876" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1224,1324,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Ogygites</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tromelin, G. de &amp; Lebesconte, P." pageId="17" pageNumber="318" pagination="683 - 687" refId="ref47881" refString="Tromelin, G. de. &amp; Lebesconte, P. (1876) Presentation de fossiles paleozoiques du department d'Ille-et-Vilaine et note additionnelle sur la faune silurianne du l'Ouest de la France. Comptes Rendus 4 me session Association Francaise Advancement Science, Nantes, 1876, 683 - 687." type="journal article" year="1876">Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte, 1876</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(type species 
<taxonomicName authority="Brongniart" authorityName="Brongniart" box="[551,894,1693,1720]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desmaresti">
<emphasis box="[551,763,1693,1720]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Ogygia desmaresti</emphasis>
Brongniart
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[905,927,1694,1719]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">in</emphasis>
Brongniart &amp; Desmarest 1822), and we are therefore obliged to discuss both genera here. The type material of the type species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte" authorityYear="1876" box="[1144,1244,1730,1756]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1144,1244,1730,1756]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Ogygites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is both distorted and incomplete, and a very detailed discussion of it by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rabano, I." box="[776,938,1765,1791]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" pagination="541 - 609" refId="ref46614" refString="Rabano, I. (1989) Trilobites del Ordovicico Medio del sector meridional de la Zona Centroiberica espanola. Part II Agnostina y Asaphida Publicaciones Especiales del Boletin Geologico y Minero, 100, 541 - 609." type="journal article" year="1989">Rabáno (1989</bibRefCitation>
. p. 76–82) concluded with placing 
<taxonomicName authority="Incertae" authorityName="Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte" authorityYear="1876" box="[1337,1437,1766,1792]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1337,1437,1766,1792]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Ogygites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘Incertae subfamiliae” within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salter" authorityYear="1864" box="[481,603,1801,1827]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Asaphidae</taxonomicName>
. She regarded the clarification of the identity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte" authorityYear="1876" box="[1135,1235,1802,1828]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1135,1235,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Ogygites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as beyond resolution and recommended restricting its usage to the distorted 
<typeStatus box="[812,914,1837,1863]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">holotype</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rabano, I." box="[923,1090,1837,1863]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" pagination="541 - 609" refId="ref46614" refString="Rabano, I. (1989) Trilobites del Ordovicico Medio del sector meridional de la Zona Centroiberica espanola. Part II Agnostina y Asaphida Publicaciones Especiales del Boletin Geologico y Minero, 100, 541 - 609." type="journal article" year="1989">Rabáno (1989)</bibRefCitation>
was unaware of a forthcoming revision of 
<taxonomicName box="[279,433,1873,1900]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desmaresti">
<emphasis box="[279,433,1873,1900]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">O. desmaresti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the type area of Angers by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pillet, J." box="[803,946,1873,1899]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" pagination="1 - 60" refId="ref46442" refString="Pillet, J. (1990) La faune des Ardoises d'Angers. Memoire de la Societe d'etudes scientifiques de l'Anjou, 7, 1 - 60." type="journal article" year="1990">Pillet (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, who attributed much additional material to the same species. Although it is distorted, much of it is articulated, and if Pillet is correct in attributing his material to 
<taxonomicName box="[180,335,1945,1972]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desmaresti">
<emphasis box="[180,335,1945,1972]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">O. desmaresti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as is likely, it is clear that the type species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte" authorityYear="1876" box="[857,957,1946,1972]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[857,957,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Ogygites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares its principal features with both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Birmanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pribyl &amp; Vanek" authorityYear="1965" box="[293,455,1981,2007]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Nobiliasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[293,455,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Nobiliasaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The pygidium is not seen on the type material, but several specimens figured by Pillet (e.g. 1990, pl. 15) prove the presence of numerous backwardly directed chevron-shaped ridges/furrows on the long and narrow pygidial axis that are clearly present also on the type specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Barrande)" baseAuthorityName="Barrande" box="[1019,1390,187,213]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Nobiliasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilis">
<emphasis box="[1019,1263,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Nobiliasaphus nobilis</emphasis>
(Barrande)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[151,438,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Pamirotechites pamiricus</emphasis>
Balashova, but not on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reed" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[690,945,223,249]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="birmanicus">
<emphasis box="[690,945,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Birmanites birmanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or other oriental species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" box="[1251,1374,223,248]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1251,1374,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Birmanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is such an unusual character that in our view it is likely a synapomorphy of species sharing it, and constitutes the defining character of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pribyl &amp; Vanek" authorityYear="1965" box="[395,557,295,321]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Nobiliasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[395,557,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Nobiliasaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte" authorityYear="1876" box="[565,665,295,321]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[565,665,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Ogygites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For example, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rabano, I." box="[836,1005,295,321]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="541 - 609" refId="ref46614" refString="Rabano, I. (1989) Trilobites del Ordovicico Medio del sector meridional de la Zona Centroiberica espanola. Part II Agnostina y Asaphida Publicaciones Especiales del Boletin Geologico y Minero, 100, 541 - 609." type="journal article" year="1989">Rabáno (1989)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated several species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1372,1436,295,321]" name="Spain" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Spain</collectingCountry>
showing this feature, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hammann, W. &amp; Leone, F." box="[441,746,331,357]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="1 - 217" refId="ref44454" refString="Hammann, W. &amp; Leone, F. (1997) Trilobites from the post-Sardic (Upper Ordovician) sequence of southern Sardinia. Part 1. Beringeria, 20, 1 - 217." type="journal article" year="1997">Hammann &amp; Leone (1997)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated others from Sardinia. One of Rabáno’s species, 
<taxonomicName class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Nobiliasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hammanni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">N. hammanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has a posterior pygidial spine, which is not considered generically significant. However unsatisfactory its type material, it is likely that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte" authorityYear="1876" box="[509,609,403,429]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[509,609,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Ogygites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the senior name for this clade. If 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" box="[1006,1129,403,428]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1006,1129,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Birmanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to species with transverse pygidial ring furrows then some species may be better placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" box="[1006,1129,439,464]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1006,1129,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Birmanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pribyl &amp; Vanek" authorityYear="1965" box="[1267,1429,439,465]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Nobiliasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1267,1429,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Nobiliasaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; for example, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hughes, 1979" authorityName="Hughes" authorityYear="1979" box="[304,722,475,501]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Nobiliasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="powysi">
<emphasis box="[304,552,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Nobiliasaphus powysi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hughes, C. P." box="[561,722,475,501]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="109 - 181" refId="ref44696" refString="Hughes, C. P. (1979) The Ordovician trilobite faunas of the Builth-Llandrindod Inlier, central Wales. Part 3. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Geology Series, 32, 109 - 181." type="journal article" year="1979">Hughes, 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Ordovician of the Builth Inlier, 
<collectingCountry box="[1206,1277,475,501]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Wales</collectingCountry>
. The range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pribyl &amp; Vanek" authorityYear="1965" box="[151,313,511,537]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Nobiliasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,313,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Nobiliasaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte" authorityYear="1876" box="[321,421,511,537]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[321,421,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Ogygites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not extend as far to the east (present geography) over Ordovician Gondwana as does that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" box="[237,360,547,572]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[237,360,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Birmanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Finally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kielan, 1960" authorityName="Kielan" authorityYear="1960" box="[471,794,547,573]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Opsimasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[471,636,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Opsimasaphus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kielan, Z." box="[646,794,547,573]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="1 - 191" refId="ref44947" refString="Kielan, Z. (1960) Upper Ordovician trilobites from Poland and some related forms from Bohemia and Scandinavia. Acta Palaeontologica Polonica, 11, 1 - 191." type="journal article" year="1960">Kielan, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(type species 
<taxonomicName authority="Kielan, 1960" authorityName="Kielan" authorityYear="1960" box="[963,1281,547,573]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Opsimasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaanussoni">
<emphasis box="[963,1121,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">O. jaanussoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kielan, Z." box="[1132,1281,547,573]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="1 - 191" refId="ref44947" refString="Kielan, Z. (1960) Upper Ordovician trilobites from Poland and some related forms from Bohemia and Scandinavia. Acta Palaeontologica Polonica, 11, 1 - 191." type="journal article" year="1960">Kielan, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" box="[151,274,583,608]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Birmanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a relatively short (sag.) pygidium—the structure of the pygidial axis (with the exception of Chinese 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lu" authorityYear="1975" box="[247,480,619,645]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Opsimasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudodawanicus">
<emphasis box="[247,480,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">O. pseudodawanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Turvey, S. T." box="[534,678,619,645]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="347 - 399" refId="ref48057" refString="Turvey, S. T. (2007) Asaphoid trilobites from the Arenig-Llanvirn of the South China Plate. Palaeontology, 50, 347 - 399. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1475 - 4983.2006.00641. x" type="journal article" year="2007">Turvey 2007</bibRefCitation>
) is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" box="[906,1029,619,644]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[906,1029,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Birmanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pribyl &amp; Vanek" authorityYear="1965" box="[1160,1322,619,645]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Nobiliasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1160,1322,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Nobiliasaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tromelin &amp; Lebesconte" authorityYear="1876" box="[1330,1430,619,645]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1330,1430,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Ogygites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the cephalic features seem to us identical to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" box="[807,930,655,680]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[807,930,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Birmanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kielan, Z." box="[945,1097,655,681]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="1 - 191" refId="ref44947" refString="Kielan, Z. (1960) Upper Ordovician trilobites from Poland and some related forms from Bohemia and Scandinavia. Acta Palaeontologica Polonica, 11, 1 - 191." type="journal article" year="1960">Kielan (1960</bibRefCitation>
, p. 75-77) gave a detailed account of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kielan" authorityYear="1960" box="[255,420,691,717]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Opsimasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[255,420,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Opsimasaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in relation to what would now be called 
<taxonomicName authority="Pribyl and Vanek, 1965" authorityName="Pribyl and Vanek" authorityYear="1965" box="[899,1342,690,717]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Nobiliasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[899,1061,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Nobiliasaphus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pribyl, A. &amp; Vanek, J." box="[1070,1342,690,717]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="277 - 282" refId="ref46547" refString="Pribyl, A. &amp; Vanek, J. (1965) Neue Trilobiten des bohmischen Ordoviziums. Vestnik Ustredniho Ustavu Geologickeho, 40, 277 - 282." type="journal article" year="1965">Přibyl and Vaněk, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but did not bring 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" box="[264,387,727,752]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,387,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Birmanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into the discussion, possibly because when she was writing this genus was still regarded as a dikelokephalinid. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chugaeva, M. N." box="[381,578,762,789]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref43103" refString="Chugaeva, M. N. (1958) Trilobites of the Ordovician of the Chu-Ili mountains. Ordovician of Kazakhstan 3. Trudy Geologicheskogo Instituta, 9, 1 - 138, 111 pls. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1958">Chugaeva (1958)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chugaeva" authorityYear="1958" box="[707,950,763,789]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Ogygites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="almatyensis">
<emphasis box="[707,950,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Ogygites almatyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1026,1160,763,789]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, which would be better placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" box="[261,384,799,824]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[261,384,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Birmanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the criteria given here. It is possible that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kielan" authorityYear="1960" box="[888,1053,799,825]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Opsimasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[888,1053,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Opsimasaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a subjective junior synonym of 
<emphasis box="[151,281,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sheng" authorityYear="1934" box="[151,277,835,860]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Birmanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Birmanites</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
as discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhou, Z. - Y. &amp; Dean, W. T." box="[469,705,835,861]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="743 - 786" refId="ref49452" refString="Zhou, Z. - Y. &amp; Dean, W. T. (1986) Ordovician trilobites from Chedao, Gansu Province, NW China. Palaeontology, 29, 743 - 786." type="journal article" year="1986">Zhou &amp; Dean (1986)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Romano, M. &amp; Owen, A. W." box="[760,1042,835,861]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="681 - 720" refId="ref46902" refString="Romano, M. &amp; Owen, A. W. (1993) Early Caradoc trilobites of eastern Ireland and their palaeogeographical significance. Palaeontology, 36, 681 - 720." type="journal article" year="1993">Romano &amp; Owen (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kielan" authorityYear="1960" box="[1123,1288,835,861]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Opsimasaphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1123,1288,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Opsimasaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was retained by 
<bibRefCitation author="Turvey, S. T." box="[186,341,871,897]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="347 - 399" refId="ref48057" refString="Turvey, S. T. (2007) Asaphoid trilobites from the Arenig-Llanvirn of the South China Plate. Palaeontology, 50, 347 - 399. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1475 - 4983.2006.00641. x" type="journal article" year="2007">Turvey (2007</bibRefCitation>
, p. 366).
</paragraph>
